    summary: "At $642M, Liberia's gross reserves now cover 4.3 months of imports — the strongest buffer since 2013. Mining royalties, diaspora inflows, and IMF SDRs all played a role. But the more important question is what the CBL does with the breathing room.",
    source: 'Central Bank of Liberia',
